<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Community - Stories with Salmon</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/community.css">
</head>
<body>
    <nav>
        <a href="/home">Home</a>
        <a href="/migration">Migration Map</a>
        <a href="/community">Community</a>
    </nav>
    
    <section class="community-intro">
        <h1>Bring Them Back: Join the Community Effort to Protect Salmon</h1>
        <p>
            The Columbia River's salmon are more than just fish — they are symbols of resilience, vital to local ecosystems, Indigenous cultures, and community livelihoods. But their future is uncertain. By sharing your salmon sightings, observations, and experiences, you help build a living archive of the river’s health. Every report brings us closer to understanding salmon migration patterns and strengthening conservation efforts.
        </p>
    </section>
    
    <section class="community-section">
        <h1>Community Stories</h1>
        <p>Explore stories from community members about their experiences and efforts in salmon conservation.</p>

        <div class="story-grid">
            <% stories.forEach(story => { %>
                <div class="story-card">
                    <h2><%= story.title %></h2>
                    <p><%= story.description %></p>
                </div>
            <% }); %>
        </div>

        <h2>Submit Your Story</h2>
        <form action="/submit-story" method="POST">
            <label for="title">Title:</label>
            <input type="text" id="title" name="title" required>

            <label for="description">Description:</label>
            <textarea id="description" name="description" rows="4" required></textarea>

            <button type="submit">Submit Story</button>
        </form>
    </section>
</body>
</html>